  "body": "### Component\r\n\r\nCast\r\n\r\n### Describe the feature you would like\r\n\r\nTo make the result of a `cast code` call a bit more readable it could be nice to give the user the option to disassemble the hex bytecode into individual opcodes.\r\n\r\nSo if the user adds the `--disassemble` flag instead of printing the hex bytecode `0x6060604052600436106100af576000357c...`\r\nIt would print the individual opcodes one per line.\r\n\r\nThis behaviour can already be achieved by piping the output of `cast code` into a 3rd party tool such as [pyevmasm](https://github.com/crytic/pyevmasm) (see screenshot), but it might be worth integrating it into forge directly.\r\n\r\nAlternatively (or additionally) we could also add `disassemble` as a separate command to cast. \r\n\r\n<img width=\"800\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/15629702/223616586-c7d23ae5-9fac-473d-b9c6-6fbd740921a6.png\">\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n### Additional context\r\n\r\n_No response_",
